The GitHub source archive ships without a pre-generated configure script, so
autoreconf must run at build time.  autoreconf looks for the AM_ICONV macro in
the system aclocal path; on AlmaLinux 10 (and other builds that lack
gettext-devel) the macro is absent and the build fails with:

  configure.ac:123: error: possibly undefined macro: AM_ICONV

Fix this by vendoring a minimal m4/iconv.m4 stub directly in the source tree.
On Linux/glibc iconv is always provided by libc itself, so LIBICONV and
LTLIBICONV can safely be empty and the only real work is confirming that
iconv_open() is reachable.

--- /dev/null
+++ b/m4/iconv.m4
@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@
+# iconv.m4 - Minimal vendor stub so autoreconf works without gettext-devel.
+#
+# On Linux/glibc iconv is part of libc; no -liconv flag is needed.
+# Platforms that ship a separate libiconv (macOS, FreeBSD, …) are not
+# targeted by this build, so the full gettext AM_ICONV logic is not required.
+
+AC_DEFUN([AM_ICONV_LINKFLAGS_BODY],
+[
+  LIBICONV=
+  LTLIBICONV=
+  AC_SUBST([LIBICONV])
+  AC_SUBST([LTLIBICONV])
+])
+
+AC_DEFUN([AM_ICONV_LINK],
+[
+  AM_ICONV_LINKFLAGS_BODY
+  LIBS="$LIBS $LIBICONV"
+])
+
+AC_DEFUN([AM_ICONV],
+[
+  AM_ICONV_LINK
+  if test "$am_cv_func_iconv" != yes; then
+    AC_CACHE_CHECK([for iconv], [am_cv_func_iconv],
+    [AC_LINK_IFELSE(
+      [AC_LANG_PROGRAM([[#include <stdlib.h>
+#include <iconv.h>]], [[iconv_t cd = iconv_open("",""); iconv(cd,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL); iconv_close(cd);]])],
+      [am_cv_func_iconv=yes],
+      [am_cv_func_iconv=no])])
+  fi
+  ICONV_CONST=
+  AC_SUBST([ICONV_CONST])
+])
